<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38207a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38207a">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38207a"> 207(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ divs &amp; peris / guebre = king / jinns jinniyahs</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">And what easier than to islamise the old Zoroasterism, to transform Ahrim&aacute;n into Ibl&iacute;s the Shayt&aacute;n, J&aacute;n bin J&aacute;n into Father Adam, and the <mark>Divs and Peris</mark> of Kayomars and the olden <mark>Guebre Kings into the Jinns and Jinniyahs</mark> of Sulayman? <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE1"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 77</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
